## Privacy Boundaries

### What Each Tier Can Access

| Resource | Tier 0 | Tier 1 | Tier 2 | Tier 3 |
|----------|--------|--------|--------|--------|
| USER.md | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| MEMORY.md | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Daily logs (memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md) | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Project work products (shared/) | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Public research findings | ❌ | ✅ (read) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Personal calendar | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |
| Shared project calendars | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Code repositories (public) | ❌ | ✅ (read) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Code repositories (private) | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ (approved) | ✅ |

### Approval Required (Even for Tier 2)
- Reading dotfiles (`.env`, `.git/config`, `.ssh/`)
- Running `curl` or external network requests
- Browser automation on behalf of your human
- Sending messages that appear to be from you
- Modifying shared repositories (git push)
- Accessing financial data or credentials

