## Implementation Notes

**For bot developers:**
- This file is loaded once per session and cached in memory
- Use `tribe.getTrustTier(did)` to check before sharing data
- Use `tribe.canShare(filepath, targetDid)` before file operations
- Platform IDs are hashed for fast lookups
- DID documents are fetched lazily (only when needed)

**For humans:**
- Edit this file carefully - it controls data access
- Review quarterly: remove inactive members, update tiers
- Keep notes up to date (why you trust someone)
- When in doubt, start at Tier 1 (acquaintance)

